description:
&lt;p&gt;This post is fixed term for 18 months due to funding&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An opportunity has arisen for an enthusiastic and innovative person to join the Bank and Roster Team. Based in Hafan Derwen Bank Office, Carmarthen, the successful candidate will undergo a period of training relevant to the role as defined below.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Working in a close team environment, you will be involved in:-&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Liaising with bank and agency workers, ward staff and agency administration teams via phone and email.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Booking both Bank and Agency Staff into an E-roster system&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Ensuring succinct and timely communication with Ward Staff in relation to bookings and cancellations.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Processing both bank timesheets and agency invoices, endorsing attendance.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Potentially dealing with initial complaints and concerns and directing these to the most appropriate manager.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Reviewing pay queries and referring these to the relevant department / team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Liaising with internal departments such as invoicing and payroll to resolve queries.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Maintaining the relevant data base in relation to potential restrictions.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Close outstanding calls when completed and / or book follow-up calls as appropriate.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Provide administration duties, to assist in the running of the bank and roster teams, when required.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Participate in specific reviews / projects if required, and perform other duties as required.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Candidates will need to have excellent customer service skills, fast accurate data entry, definitive knowledge of emails and a good geographical knowledge.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ability to speak Welsh is desirable for this post; English and/or Welsh speakers are equally welcome to apply.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Office cover is Monday to Sunday including bank holidays.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Interviews will be held on 17th November 2020.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
